* {{a|UK|US}} {{enPR|rīt}}, {{IPA|/ɹaɪt/}}, {{SAMPA|/raIt/}}
* {{audio|en-us-write.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪt}}

====Homophones====
* [[right]], [[rite]], [[wright]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|writes|writing|'''[[wrote]]''' ''or archaic'', '''[[writ]]'''|written}}

# {{context|transitive|intransitive}} To form letters, words or symbols on a surface in order to communicate.
#: ''The pupil '''wrote''' his name on the paper.''
#: ''Your son has been '''writing''' on the wall.''
# {{transitive}} To be the author of (a book, article, poem, etc.).
#: ''My uncle '''writes''' newspaper articles for The Herald.''
# {{context|transitive|US}} To send a letter to.
#: ''Please '''write''' me when you get there.''
# {{transitive}} Show facts, to make things clear.
#: ''The due day of the homework is '''written''' in the syllabus.''
# {{intransitive}} To be an author.
#: ''I '''write''' for a living.''
# {{context|intransitive|computing}} record data by a machine, especially for spindols.
#: ''The '''write''' speed of the disk is usually lower than the read speed.''

